<h1>Actions</h1>
<%- if @message -%>
<p class="msg"><%= h(@message) %></p>
<%- end -%>
<p class="muted">Every action runs through the same lock as scheduled runs — a click can never
start a second concurrent pipeline. Long actions run in the background; results appear in the
job list below. Restores are CLI-only by design.</p>

<form class="action" method="post" action="/actions/backup">
  <h3>Backup now</h3>
  <p>Run the full dump → compress → encrypt → fan-out pipeline.</p>
  <input type="hidden" name="_csrf" value="<%= h(@csrf_token) %>">
  <p>
    <label>Database
      <select name="database">
        <option value="">(all)</option>
        <%- @database_names.each do |name| -%>
        <option value="<%= h(name) %>"><%= h(name) %></option>
        <%- end -%>
      </select>
    </label>
  </p>
  <p>Destinations <span class="muted">(none checked = all)</span></p>
  <p>
    <%- @destinations.each do |dest| -%>
    <label class="dest"><input type="checkbox" name="destinations[]" value="<%= h(dest.token) %>"> <%= h(dest.label) %></label>
    <%- end -%>
  </p>
  <p><label><input type="checkbox" name="confirm"> I want to start a backup run</label></p>
  <button type="submit">Backup</button>
</form>

<form class="action" method="post" action="/actions/verify">
  <h3>Verify latest backups</h3>
  <p>Tier 1 checksum + Tier 2 structural check; deep restores into a scratch database.</p>
  <input type="hidden" name="_csrf" value="<%= h(@csrf_token) %>">
  <p><label><input type="checkbox" name="deep"> Deep (Tier 3 scratch-restore)</label></p>
  <p><label><input type="checkbox" name="confirm"> I want to verify the latest backups</label></p>
  <button type="submit">Verify</button>
</form>

<form class="action" method="post" action="/actions/prune">
  <h3>Prune</h3>
  <p>Enforce the retention policy. Dry run unless "apply" is checked.</p>
  <input type="hidden" name="_csrf" value="<%= h(@csrf_token) %>">
  <p><label><input type="checkbox" name="apply"> Apply (actually delete)</label></p>
  <p><label><input type="checkbox" name="confirm"> I understand what prune will delete</label></p>
  <button type="submit">Prune</button>
</form>

<form class="action" method="post" action="/actions/test-notification">
  <h3>Send a test notification</h3>
  <p>Dispatch a test summary through every configured notifier.</p>
  <input type="hidden" name="_csrf" value="<%= h(@csrf_token) %>">
  <p><label><input type="checkbox" name="confirm"> Send it</label></p>
  <button type="submit">Test notification</button>
</form>

<form class="action" method="post" action="/actions/doctor">
  <h3>Run doctor</h3>
  <p>Re-check tools, config, storage destinations, and database connectivity.</p>
  <input type="hidden" name="_csrf" value="<%= h(@csrf_token) %>">
  <p><label><input type="checkbox" name="confirm"> Run the checks</label></p>
  <button type="submit">Doctor</button>
</form>

<h2>Trigger remotely</h2>
<p class="muted">Kick off the same actions from a script, webhook, cron on another host, or a phone
shortcut. Authenticate with the dashboard token as a Bearer credential; the call returns a job id
you can poll. Requires a <span class="mono">web.auth.token</span> (browser basic-auth can't reach
these endpoints).</p>
<pre class="mono"># Back up one database to just the NAS and Google Drive:
curl -sS -X POST https://HOST/api/actions/backup \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $PGKEEPER_WEB_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"database":"app_production","destinations":["nas","gdrive"]}'

# Poll the job it returned, or list recent jobs:
curl -sS https://HOST/api/jobs/1     -H "Authorization: Bearer $PGKEEPER_WEB_TOKEN"
curl -sS https://HOST/api/jobs        -H "Authorization: Bearer $PGKEEPER_WEB_TOKEN"
curl -sS https://HOST/api/destinations -H "Authorization: Bearer $PGKEEPER_WEB_TOKEN"</pre>

<h2>Jobs</h2>
<%- if @jobs.empty? -%>
<p class="muted">No jobs yet.</p>
<%- else -%>
<table>
  <tr><th>#</th><th>Action</th><th>Status</th><th>Started</th><th>Finished</th><th>Detail</th></tr>
  <%- @jobs.each do |job| -%>
  <tr>
    <td><%= job.id %></td>
    <td class="mono"><%= h(job.action) %></td>
    <td><%= pill(job.status, { running: 'warn', done: 'ok', failed: 'bad' }.fetch(job.status, '')) %></td>
    <td><%= h(fmt_time(job.started_at)) %></td>
    <td><%= job.finished_at ? h(fmt_time(job.finished_at)) : "-" %></td>
    <td><%= h(job.detail || "") %></td>
  </tr>
  <%- end -%>
</table>
<p class="muted">Refresh the page to see job progress.</p>
<%- end -%>
